        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Macaw</placeName>
                <date>October 28. 1856</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev: I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">We have here in<lb/>
                <placeName>Macaw</placeName> improved our Burial Ground<lb/> in building around it a
                brick wall and<lb/> setting Iron doors. We have formed ourself<lb/> into a Society
                for that object also for<lb/> charitable purposes. Now I would like<lb/> to dedicate
                the burial ground with suitable<lb/> prayers and therefore respectfully request<lb/>
                you to give me a synopsis of the<lb/> proceedings with the appropriate prayers<lb/>
                for the <sic>ocasion</sic>. Will you also have the<lb/> kindness to send me the
                account of my<lb/> indebtedness to you for the occident. I know<lb/> that I owe you
                besides the half yearly<lb/> subscription of <persName>Mr.
                Feuchswanger</persName>.<lb/> My son <persName>Naphtaly</persName> will hand you
                this<lb/> letter. He lately returned from <placeName>California</placeName><lb/>
                Wishing you health and prosperity</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>I remain dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your very obedient Servant and friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">A Dessan</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
